 the German Romantics, providing a valuable guide to a major text that has yet to appear in English translation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aLiterary Studies -- General Criticism and Theory. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh1 aDüttmann, Alexander Garcia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFenves, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerris, David S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerris, David S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFrey, Hans-]ost, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGasché, Rodolphe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacobs, Carol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCall, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNagele, Rainer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeber, Samuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361587840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503615878423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503615878/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles